sections.title: How the population has changed in Cotswold
sections.label: Select another area to see how the population has changed

sections.content: In 2020, Cotswold was the 23rd largest local authority in the South West, with a total population of 90,264. An increase compared with 2019.

sections.title: Largest local authorities in the South West, 2002-2020
Population density in Cotswold
sections.content: In 2020, the population density in Cotswold was 78 people per square kilometre, which was less than the South West (237), and less than the United Kingdom as a whole (276).

sections.title: Densest local authorities in the South West, 2020
Median age in Cotswold
sections.content: In 2020, the median age in Cotswold was 49 years, which was older than the South West (44 years), and older than the United Kingdom as a whole (41 years).
